      <p>Welcome to the home page for the inaugural Hellenic-American Meeting of Early-Career Researchers (HAmMER), to be held on May 10th,
         2025, on the MIT Campus!<br /><br />
         
         Co-organized by a committee of students from Boston-area academic institutions, the symposium
         is envisioned and supported by the <a href="https://www.hellenic-academics.org/">Circle of 
         Hellenic Academics in Boston</a>, a non-profit aiming to connect academics of Hellenic descent.<br /><br />
         
         The event is mostly envisioned for PhD and early career researchers, loosely defined as within 
         5 years from the completion of their PhD degree, to share their research in a short talk 
         with other researchers of Hellenic descent in a similar career stage. Research presentations 
         in any area of science, engineering and humanities are welcome! <br /><br />
         
         Depending on the number of submissions, we may also feature a poster session.
      </p>
